-- U.K. Parliament Break-in Investigated by London’s City Police
-- B y   G a v i n   F i n c h
-- 2012-03-17T10:56:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-17/u-k-parliament-break-in-investigated-by-london-s-city-police.html
Police in  London  are investigating
a report of a break-in at the Houses of Parliament yesterday.  “Police were called following reports of a forced entry at
the Palace of Westminster at 6:55 p.m. last night,” an official
at the Metropolitan Police said. “It’s being investigated.”  The reported break-in was at offices used by the opposition
 Labour Party  leader Ed Miliband, according to the Press
Association news agency. A Labour spokeswoman declined to
comment while the police investigation was continuing.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gavin Finch in London at 
